.TH "update_tasks_cpumask" 9 "update_tasks_cpumask" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
update_tasks_cpumask \- Update the cpumasks of tasks in the cpuset.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" update_tasks_cpumask
.BI "(struct cpuset *cs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cs" 12
the cpuset in which each task's cpus_allowed mask needs to be changed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Iterate through each task of \fIcs\fP updating its cpus_allowed to the
effective cpuset's.  As this function is called with cpuset_mutex held,
cpuset membership stays stable.
